## Content Types: Blog vs Documentation

While both use our voice, blogs and documentation serve different purposes.

### Documentation (Guides, References, Tutorials)

**Purpose:** Teach concepts and enable tasks that remain relevant over time.

- Evergreen content—minimize time-sensitive references
- Comprehensive coverage of a topic
- Structured for reference and re-reading
- Neutral on vendor choices unless specifically comparing
- Updated when technology changes

### Blog Posts

**Purpose:** Share insights, experiences, and timely perspectives.

- Can be more personal and opinionated
- Time-stamped and context-specific ("In 2024, we saw...")
- Can reference current events, trends, announcements
- Shorter, more focused scope
- Doesn't need to cover everything—can be a single insight
- Can be more experimental in format

**Blog-specific techniques:**
- Stronger hooks—compete for attention
- More personality in the opening
- Can end with questions or calls for discussion
- Can reference "last week" or "recently"
- Can take stronger stances

