## Linking Strategy

### Internal Links

**Link generously within your documentation:**
- First mention of a concept that's explained elsewhere
- Prerequisites the reader might need
- Related topics for deeper exploration

**Link text should describe the destination:**
- Good: "See the [deployment strategies guide](./deployment-strategies)"
- Bad: "Click [here](./deployment-strategies) for more"

**Don't over-link:**
- Link once per section, not every mention
- Don't link common terms (Git, Docker) unless to your own explanation
- Don't link within headings

### External Links

**When to link externally:**
- Official documentation for tools/libraries
- Original sources for research or quotes
- Specifications and standards

**External link best practices:**
- Prefer official/stable URLs over blog posts
- For critical information, summarize the key point—don't rely solely on the link
- Consider whether the link will survive (avoid URL shorteners)

