## Accessibility & Global Audience

### Write Inclusively

- Use gender-neutral language ("they" not "he/she")
- Avoid idioms and culture-specific references that don't translate
- Avoid directional language ("above", "below") that fails in non-visual contexts
- Use descriptive link text: "Read the deployment guide" not "Click here"

### Accessible Formatting

- Provide alt text for images
- Use semantic heading hierarchy (don't skip levels)
- Ensure sufficient color contrast in diagrams
- Don't rely on color alone to convey meaning

### International Readers

- Spell out abbreviations on first use
- Use unambiguous date formats (January 15, 2025, not 1/15/25)
- Avoid humor that requires cultural context
- Keep sentence structure simple for non-native speakers

